Aegis Holds Talks With Ipsos on Synovate Sale, Telegraph Says

-- B y   E m m a   C h a r l t o n
-- 
2011-06-05T05:33:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-05/aegis-holds-talks-with-ipsos-on-synovate-sale-telegraph-says.html
Aegis Group Plc (AGS)  held talks with
polling company  Ipsos (IPS)  SA about selling its 500 million-pound
($821 million) market research unit, Synovate, the Sunday
Telegraph  reported , without saying where it got the information.  The two companies met last week to discuss the sale, the
newspaper reported. Market research firm  GfK SE (GFK) ,  Publicis Groupe
SA (PUB)  and  WPP Plc (WPP)  will probably also be interested in Synovate,
according to the Sunday Telegraph.  UBS AG (UBSN)  is advising Ipsos,
while Greenhill & Co. is advising Aegis, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Emma Charlton in London at 
 echarlton1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dick Schumacher at 
 dschumacher@bloomberg.net . 